##Hong Kong
###Hong Kong: Airmail
These series of articles are based on personal research through auction catalogues, books and exhibitors. The first published source of information on the air mail service originated in Lobdell and Hopkins. However this is fairly incomplete and does not cover well the first experimental flights and associated air mail areas, such as disaster mail.

The first air mail to Hong Kong was from the experimental flight in 1925 from England.

