###August 1924, Summer Air Service, London - Moscow
In late August 1924 British airmail was first accepted for Hong Kong. It was first carried by Imperial Airways to Berlin and then by Deutsche Russiche Luftverkehregesellsschaft, usually known as Deruluft, to Moscow, from where it was transported by the Trans-Siberian railway to Manchouli, by rail to Shanghai, and then by sea to Hong Kong. This service was only available in the summer, being suspended in the winter due to the weather.

