### 1936 China National Aviation Company
On 5 November 1936, an air mail service was inaugurated by the China National Aviation Company (C.N.A.C) between Hong Kong and a number of places in China. No official device was used to mark the opening of the service, which used the Type 19, circular datestamp. The cover can be found quite easily and should retail about $15.00.

