###1937 Transpacific Air Mail Service

The 21 April 1937 brought the inauguration of a transpacific air mail service operated by Pan-American Airways. The service started from San Francisco and terminated at Macao, stopping at Guam, Honolulu, Manila and Hong Kong an route. The mail for Hong Kong carried on this first flight was received on teh 28 April and each cover bore an interesting cachet applied in blue containing the words <span style="font-size:smaller">FIRST FLIGHT TO ASIA F.A.M No. 14 SAN FRANSCISCO TO HONG KONG.</span>

